verbs.description: reblock (third-person singular simple present reblocks, present participle reblocking, simple past and past participle reblocked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To block, prevent, or hamper again.
examples: It is not just bad news about Dubai that gets blocked from the Internet;  […]  a whole range of other social networking sites have been blocked, unblocked and reblocked.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remould (a hat) into its original shape.
examples: Reputable dry cleaners can clean and reblock a hat.

entries.meaning: (transitive, theater) To block, or specify the position of, (actors on the stage) again.
examples: In less than five hours the actors will perform the ballroom scene, rewritten and reblocked.
